	<div id="39297" class="singlecomment"><div class="commenthead">Laura Miller <div class="commentdate">April  9, 2007</div></div> <div class="commentbox"><p>A trip to Helsinki introduced me to the wonders of the Finnish egg sandwich: perfectly cooked eggs (with an extra yolk or two) mashed with perfectly softened butter and a little salt, spread on delicious wholegrain bread. This treatment goes down particularly well with little kids and is very comforting to egg-loving grown-ups, too.</p></div></div>
		  <div class="commentdivide">&nbsp;</div><br clear=all />
	<div id="39298" class="singlecomment"><div class="commenthead">Cindy Taylor <div class="commentdate">April  9, 2007</div></div> <div class="commentbox"><p>My "friend" and I were making deviled eggs one night - and we started adding a little of what seemed like everything - they were the BEST - but what was left over made the best egg salad sandwich I had ever eaten.  </p>

<p>We added fresh bacon bits - a small amount, finely chopped peppers, onions, sour cream, mayo and just a little ranch dressing.  Then we added chili powder, salt, pepper and peprica.  The peppers that time were mild, but since we have added some hot peppers - they are GREAT.</p></div></div>
