	<div id="39401" class="singlecomment"><div class="commenthead">Cait <div class="commentdate">April  9, 2007</div></div> <div class="commentbox"><p>I also have a texture-based aversion to regular egg salad and I agree that the mayo-to-egg ratio is key. To minimize the amount of mayo in the salad, I separate the boiled eggs, mashing the yolks first and adding a wee bit of mayo, just to make them creamy, and then coarsely mashing in the whites. The mayo gets evenly distributed and you avoid the mayo overload that is the death of a good egg salad. Re: spices and add-ins, I defer to the other egg salad experts in the field. Enjoy the eggs!</p></div></div>
